## Interactive Artifact Version

When the user asks for a dashboard, interactive view, or visual:
- Build a **React artifact** (JSX) with:
  - Tab navigation: Overview | Schemes | Analytics | Hidden Gems
  - Search/filter bar
  - Expandable scheme cards
  - Bar/pie charts using recharts
  - Color-coded status badges
- Use Tailwind classes for styling
- Fetch data inline (hardcoded from search results since live API not available in artifact)

Refer to `scripts/scheme-extractor.js` for the data structure to embed in the artifact.

### 🔗 LINK RENDERING IN REACT ARTIFACTS — CRITICAL RULES

**NEVER use `window.open()` or `onClick` handlers for external navigation** — these are blocked in sandboxed artifact environments and buttons will silently do nothing.

**ALWAYS use `<a>` tags for all external links:**

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT — always works
<a
  href={scheme.official_link}
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"
  className="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-3 py-1 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700"
>
  🔗 Apply Now ↗
</a>

// ❌ WRONG — silently fails in artifact sandbox
<button onClick={() => window.open(scheme.official_link, '_blank')}>Apply</button>

// ❌ WRONG — silently fails in artifact sandbox
<button onClick={() => { window.location.href = scheme.official_link }}>Apply</button>
```

**URL validation before rendering:**
```jsx
// Always validate URL before rendering a link
const isValidUrl = (url) => {
  if (!url || url === 'null' || url === 'N/A' || url === '') return false;
  try { new URL(url); return true; } catch { return false; }
};

// Render with fallback
const SchemeLink = ({ url, name }) => {
  const finalUrl = isValidUrl(url)
    ? url
    : `https://www.google.com/search?q=${encodeURIComponent(name + ' official apply')}`;
  const label = isValidUrl(url) ? '🔗 Apply Now ↗' : '🔍 Find Apply Link ↗';
  return (
    <a href={finalUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
       className="text-blue-600 underline hover:text-blue-800 text-sm">
      {label}
    </a>
  );
};
```
